Title: Retriever Triad (GSHP / Lab / Golden) — Recall Recovery System v1.0

⸻

Core Insight

When recall fails, don’t force reconstruction—
deploy specialized retrieval agents that recover memory through different pathways.

Hound = detects anomaly
Retrievers = recover signal

⸻

System Architecture

1) Hound (already exists)

* Detects:
    * recall failure
    * inconsistency
    * missing signal
* Triggers:
    Retriever deployment

⸻

2) Retriever Triad (Recovery Layer)

A) GSHP — Precision Pointer (German Shorthaired Pointer)

Role: Locate exact signal via structure

* Method:
    * pattern matching
    * schema lookup
    * index-based retrieval
* Strength:
    * fast, targeted recall
* Weakness:
    * fails if encoding is weak or misaligned

Use when:

* you know the structure
* you’re close to the answer
* recall is “on the tip of your tongue”

⸻

B) Labrador — Context Diver

Role: Recover via surrounding context

* Method:
    * semantic association
    * related ideas
    * environmental cues
* Strength:
    * finds signal through proximity
* Weakness:
    * can bring back noise with signal

Use when:

* you remember the situation not the detail
* context is available
* GSHP fails

⸻

C) Golden Retriever — Pattern Reconstructor

Role: Rebuild missing signal from learned patterns

* Method:
    * inference
    * generalization
    * probabilistic reconstruction
* Strength:
    * works when signal is missing entirely
* Weakness:
    * risk of drift / hallucination

Use when:

* no direct recall
* context incomplete
* last resort before failure

⸻

Execution Flow

Hound detects failure →

1. GSHP (direct retrieval attempt)
2. If fail → Labrador (context sweep)
3. If fail → Golden (pattern reconstruction)
4. If still uncertain → Flag + verify

⸻

Equation Integration

Recall ≈ f(Cue × Pathway × State)

Retriever Triad expands:

Pathway redundancy

⸻

Design Principles

1. Never rely on one retrieval path
2. Escalate from precise → broad → generative
3. Always verify Golden outputs
4. Use cues to guide which retriever leads
5. Measure which retriever succeeds (feedback loop)

⸻

Failure Modes

* GSHP overfitting to wrong index
* Labrador noise contamination
* Golden hallucination drift
* Skipping escalation order
* No verification step

